<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1279,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
This species was previously known only from the 
<collectingCountry box="[861,1021,1279,1305]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">United States</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1034,1163,1279,1305]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1222,1319,1279,1305]" name="Panama" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Panamá</collectingCountry>
. Now it is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[751,822,1319,1345]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Pará).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1279,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Diagnosis. Mandibles edentate; third antennal segment 
<number box="[959,996,1359,1385]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="2.2">2.2</number>
X as long as wide; flagellar pubescence very short and subapressed; WH 
<number box="[811,862,1399,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="0.97">0.97</number>
X LH; WF 
<number box="[1015,1133,1399,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.05" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.9">0.90–1.20</number>
X HE; anterior angle of ocellar triangle obtuse; pronotal disc 
<number box="[816,904,1439,1465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.55" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.6</number>
X as wide as long; propodeal disc 
<number box="[264,382,1479,1505]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" value="1.27" valueMax="1.34" valueMin="1.2">1.20–1.34</number>
as wide as long, with five strong carinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1323,1279,1665]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Variation. Clypeus dark brown; mandibles castaneous; antennae dark brown; coxae, femora and tibiae dark brown, tarsi light castaneous; metasoma black.</paragraph>
